yearly, at- Pentecost, an account of his receipts and expenses in his peculiar office. To the sacrist, for

instance, were appropriated certain tithes and revenues to defray the expenses incidental to the performance of divine service in the church, the purchase of robeS, and the repairs of the fabric. Every other department had its respective head, but all accounted to the Bursar ς*
